What goes into Lithium Ion Battery production & why does China dominate the field so much?

1st, it starts w/ extraction technology from Brine/Salt Lake & Spodumene/rock. China has raised Li recovery rate from 75% to 90% in its Qinghai Brine project.

Despite not having world's https://t.co/EZNhhNCsGg

tweets.author: tphuang
tweets.text:
Optical Transceiver mkt is also super hot.
According to HGTech, its AI high speed optical module order is full until Q4.

Both its Wuahn & Thailand bases are in full operation even during CNY period. It has started mass delivery of 1.6T modules. https://t.co/EBQnFEstLG

tweets.author: tphuang
tweets.text:
Next stage is refining & China really dominates this stage. Higher purity Li concentrate can be used to produce higher end cathode.

Can use Sulfuric Acid or Causticizing Process. By this pt, China does have its own supply chain across refining including the chemical & machines. https://t.co/CzmiDOYHl6

tweets.author: tphuang
tweets.text:
Refined Lithium can be used for LFP or NCM cathode production. Starts w/ precursor mixing of LiCO2 w/ Iron Phosphate or NCM to do reactions.

Using high temperature sintering inside kiln to produce lattice which is then crushed into cathode material powder used in batteries. https://t.co/5LtBfBjVzK

tweets.author: tphuang
tweets.text:
Batteries is the critical tech of electrification & an industry that doesn't get enough attention in the West.

While many part of its complexity like the chemistry, production process & advanced control chips mirror the complexity of semi production, it's never regarded as such.

tweets.author: tphuang
tweets.text:
A diagram below of the various chips used in the battery system, including AFEs that measure current, control voltage, do safety protection & daisy chain communication.
MCUs that control other chips & SBC chip that communicate via CAN Bus.
BMS is complicated stuff. https://t.co/TBcZzvfpFr
